Apple has released the iOS 12 developer preview, which appears to have confirmed that Face ID is coming to the iPad, The Verge reported. Citing a tweet from developer Guilherme Rambo, the report stated that the functionality discovered in iOS 12 hints at the feature that has been rumoured to be coming several times – the iPad Pro receiving Face ID support. The tweet shows that iOS 12 has hidden menus for setting up Face ID, and a section in the Settings app. Based on Rambo’s discovery, and credible rumours that were previously reported, an iPad with Face ID sensors is expected to be be launched this year. 